<div class="info-page">
  <section class="info-section">
    <p>
      <strong>VSCN</strong> — Visual Science Communication Network — is a growing network for people who
      want to make science more visual, accessible, and engaging. It brings together scientists, illustrators,
      designers, communicators, and anyone working where knowledge meets visual culture.
    </p>
    <p>
      By growing this community, we hope to encourage exchange, make collaboration easier, and
      create a place where people can find partners for visual science communication projects.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section">
    <h2 class="info-heading">What we're building toward</h2>
    <ul class="info-list">
      <li>A directory of science communicators and illustrators you can actually browse</li>
      <li>Events, online and in person, for the community to meet and collaborate</li>
      <li>A place to surface and celebrate strong visual science communication</li>
      <li>Connections between the sciences, design, illustration, and storytelling</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section">
    <h2 class="info-heading">We just got started</h2>
    <p>
      This is early days. If you want to help build VSCN, whether through design, development,
      community organising, or simply by sharing ideas, please reach out. The more people who shape
      this, the better it will become.
    </p>
    <a href="mailto:info@vscn.ch" class="info-contact">Get in touch via info@vscn.ch</a>
  </section>
</div>

